      "explanation": "For h(t) = at² + bt + c, the maximum height occurs at t = -b/(2a). Substitute this time back into h(t) to find the maximum height. The answer is 105 ft at t=2.5s. The other options — '80 ft at t=3s', '100 ft at t=2s', and '5 ft at t=0' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
